values: To dare means to be brave enough to try something.
He dared to jump out of the airplane and skydive.

to have the courage to do something

To dare is to have the courage or audacity to do something or to challenge someone to do something.
Dare means to have the courage or audacity to do something, often in defiance of rules or social norms.
n. 挑战；挑动,vt. 敢冒；不惧,vi. 敢；胆敢
